sentence: Tractor Supply Company ( TSCO ) will begin trading ex-dividend on August 13, 2015.
A cash dividend payment of $0.2 per share is scheduled to be paid on September 01, 2015.
Shareholders who purchased TSCO prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment.
This represents an 25% increase over the same period a year ago.
At the current stock price of $93.47, the dividend yield is .86%.
The previous trading day's last sale of TSCO was $93.47, representing a -2.92% decrease from the 52 week high of $96.28 and a 67.06% increase over the 52 week low of $55.95.
TSCO is a part of the Consumer Services sector, which includes companies such as Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) and Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ).
TSCO's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $2.9.
Zacks Investment Research reports TSCO's forecasted earnings growth in 2015 as 15.58%, compared to an industry average of 8.4%.
For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the TSCO Dividend History page.
